Firefighters are tackling a blaze at a multi-storey block of flats in Glasgow.
The fire broke out at the flats in Charles Street in the Springburn area at about 17:30 on Sunday.
More than 40 firefighters are involved in bringing the blaze under control. There were no reports of injuries.
A spokesman for the fire service said firefighters wearing breathing apparatus and using water jets were conducting a search of the building. 
